Derivatives For Energy Professionals
April 9-10, 2002

The energy markets have experienced tremendous price fluctuations over the past few years as well as upheaval in the over-the-counter markets. The need for energy professionals to understand derivatives, and to measure and mitigate risk is even greater than ever. 

Valuing Market Risk
Buying and Selling Forward
Hedging Long and Short Positions
Hedging Spreads and Basis
Volatility and Options
Hedging with Options
Hedging with "Exotics"
Dealing with Credit Risk

